==English==

===Etymology===
From Middle English from the Old French word ''chevalerie''. Derived from Medieval Latin ''caballerius'' and Late Latin ''caballarius'' meaning [[horseman]], and ''caballus'' meaning horse.

===Pronunciation===
*(US)
**{{IPA|/ˈʃɪvəlri/}}
**{{SAMPA|/"SIv@lri/}}

===Noun===
'''chivalry'''

#An ethical code that was prevalent in Medieval [[Europe]].  It was the honor code of the [[knight]]


Its primary virtues were:
* [[Mercy]] (Towards the poor and oppressed. They were supposed to be harsh with evil-doers.)
* [[Humility]]
* [[Honor]]
* [[Sacrifice]]
* Fear of [[God]]
* [[Faithfulness]]
* [[Courage]]
* Utmost graciousness and courtesy to ladies

